==English==
[[Image:Map of USA highlighting Nevada.png|thumb|right|Map of US highlighting Nevada]]
===Etymology===
Spanish ''[[nevada]]'', snow-covered

===Pronunciation===
<!-- Not sure if /ʌ/ is the right vowel.  English vowels are confusing. -->
Typically pronounced /nʌ'vɑdɑ/ by non-residents, /nʌ'vædɑ/ by residents.  (Residents often regard the pronunciation as a test of whether visitors, such as presidential candidates, have informed themselves about the state.)  The original [[w:Spanish language|Spanish]] pronunciation is /ne'β̞að̞a/

===Proper noun===
'''Nevada'''

#A {{USstate}} Capital: [[Carson City]].

